\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Recall that LP is written as:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{x}{min}\ \ x\T x
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\text{s.t \ensuremath{Gx\preceq h,\ Ax=b}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the linear conic programming formulation:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
K=\mathbb{R}^{d}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{1}(x)=h-Gx
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
h_{1}(x)=b-Ax
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notice that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{d}$
\end_inset

 is a cone, and that both 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{1},h_{1}$
\end_inset

 are affine, and so:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Ax=b\iff h_{1}(x)=0\ \ \ ,\ \ Gx\preceq h\iff f_{1}(x)\in K
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As for SOCP:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
c=f
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
h_{1}(x)=Cx-d
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{i}(x)=\begin{bmatrix}A_{i}\\
c\T
\end{bmatrix}x+\begin{bmatrix}b_{i}\\
d_{i}
\end{bmatrix}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As we can see both 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{i},h_{1}$
\end_inset

 are affine and so:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\norm A_{i}x+b_{i}\norm\le c_{i}\T x+d_{i}\iff
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{bmatrix}A_{i}x+b_{i}\\
c_{i}\T x+d_{i}
\end{bmatrix}\in K\iff
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{bmatrix}A_{i}\\
c\T
\end{bmatrix}x+\begin{bmatrix}b_{i}\\
d_{i}
\end{bmatrix}\in K
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lets look at each row of the problem:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{x}{min}\ c\T x
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s.t\ \ A_{i}x\le b_{i}\ \forall A\in\mathcal{A}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And for each scalar we get:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{x}{min}\ \ c\T x
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{A\in\mathcal{A}}{max}A_{i}x\le b_{i}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notice that :
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
A_{i,j}\le\hat{A_{i,j}}x_{j}+V_{i,j}x_{j}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
and that inequality holds for each coordinate.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In fact we get that :
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{A\in\mathcal{A}}{maxA_{i}x}=\hat{A_{i}}+V_{i}|x|
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lets denote 
\begin_inset Formula $z=|x|$
\end_inset

 and write the problem as:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\hat{A}x+Vz\le b
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s.t\ \ -z\le x\le z
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We can say that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P_{i}=UD_{i}^{1}U\T
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
G=UD_{i}^{2}U\T
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And so:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sum_{i}x_{i}UD_{i}^{1}U\T+UD_{i}^{2}U\T\preceq0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And getting 
\begin_inset Formula $U,U\T$
\end_inset

 to the sides we get:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U\sum(x_{i}D_{i}^{1}+D^{2})U\T\le0\rightarrow\sum(x_{i}D_{i}^{1}+D^{2})\le0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $D^{1},D^{2}$
\end_inset

 are both diagonal we can fit their values in 1d vectors
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
and so we get that we can rearrange the problem:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\hat{D}^{1}x\le-D^{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Which is LP.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
3.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
set 
\begin_inset Formula $z=\begin{bmatrix}R(x)\\
I(x)
\end{bmatrix}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
for 
\begin_inset Formula $p=1:$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{x}{min}\norm x\norm_{1}\ \ s.t\ \ Ax=b
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\underset{z\in\mathbb{R}^{2n}}{min}\sum_{i=1}^{n}\norm z_{i}...z_{i+n}\norm_{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s.t:\begin{bmatrix}R(A) & \ \ -I(A)\\
I(A) & R(A)
\end{bmatrix},z=\begin{bmatrix}R(b)\\
I(b)
\end{bmatrix}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\underset{z\in\mathbb{R}^{2n},t\in\mathbb{R}}{min}1\T t
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s.t:\begin{bmatrix}R(A) & \ \ -I(A)\\
I(A) & R(A)
\end{bmatrix},z=\begin{bmatrix}R(b)\\
I(b)
\end{bmatrix},\norm z_{i}...z_{i+n}\norm_{2}\le t
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space \space{}
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
for 
\begin_inset Formula $p=2:$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{x}{min}\norm x\norm\ \ s.t\ \ Ax=b
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\underset{z\in\mathbb{R}^{2n}}{min}\norm z\norm_{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s.t:\begin{bmatrix}R(A) & \ \ -I(A)\\
I(A) & R(A)
\end{bmatrix},z=\begin{bmatrix}R(b)\\
I(b)
\end{bmatrix}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\underset{z\in\mathbb{R}^{2n},t\in\mathbb{R}}{min}t
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s.t:\begin{bmatrix}R(A) & \ \ -I(A)\\
I(A) & R(A)
\end{bmatrix},z=\begin{bmatrix}R(b)\\
I(b)
\end{bmatrix},\norm z\norm_{2}\le t
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space \space{}
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
for 
\begin_inset Formula $p=\infty:$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\underset{x}{min}\norm x\norm_{\infty}\ \ s.t\ \ Ax=b
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\underset{z\in\mathbb{R}^{2n}}{min}\norm z\norm_{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\underset{z\in\mathbb{R}^{2n}}{min}max\norm z_{i}...z_{i+n}\norm_{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s.t:\begin{bmatrix}R(A) & \ \ -I(A)\\
I(A) & R(A)
\end{bmatrix},z=\begin{bmatrix}R(b)\\
I(b)
\end{bmatrix}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\underset{z\in\mathbb{R}^{2n},t\in\mathbb{R}}{min}t
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s.t:\begin{bmatrix}R(A) & \ \ -I(A)\\
I(A) & R(A)
\end{bmatrix},z=\begin{bmatrix}R(b)\\
I(b)
\end{bmatrix},\norm z_{i}...z_{i+n}\norm_{2}\le t
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
4.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\norm A^{*}q\norm=\norm\frac{uq\T}{\norm u\norm\cdot\norm q\norm}q\norm=\norm q\norm
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
also:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\norm Aq\norm\le\norm A\norm_{F}\cdot\norm q\norm\le\norm q\norm\rightarrow\underset{\norm A\norm_{F}\le1}{max\norm Aq\norm}\le\norm q\norm
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And together with 
\begin_inset Formula $\norm A^{*}q\norm=\norm q\norm$
\end_inset

 we get that 
\begin_inset Formula $\underset{\norm A\norm_{F}\le1}{max\norm Aq\norm}=\norm q\norm$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
2.
\end_layout

